Official site: link
Interface language: Russian, English and others

Treatment: not required

System requirements:

Microsoft® Windows® XP (32 bit), Windows Server 2008 (32 bit), Windows Vista® (32 bit), Windows 7 (32 bit and 64 bit), Windows 8 (32 bit and 64 bit), or Windows Server 2012 (64 bit)
2.33GHz or Intel® Atom ™ 1.6GHz or faster processor for netbooks
Internet Explorer 8.0 or later, Mozilla Firefox 17 or later, Google Chrome, or Opera 11
512MB of RAM (1GB of RAM recommended for netbooks); 128MB of graphics memory


Description:
Adobe® Flash® Player is a plugin for Internet Explorer, AOL, Firefox, Mozilla, Netscape and Opera browsers that allows you to play Flash movies (SWF files). Without this program, the browser will incorrectly display web pages and interactive web elements developed using Flash technology. Adobe® Flash® Player is a browser-based cross-platform runtime for delivering dynamic applications, content and video to various screens and browsers. The Flash Player environment is optimized for creating high-performance mobile applications and supports the original functionality of devices, providing user experience with the applications created.
Additional Information:

Starting with version 11.3, the universal installer allows you to install both 32-bit and 64-bit versions of Flash Player.

Adobe Flash Player - a Flash file player (SWF files), has three types of distribution:
for Internet Explorer
for Firefox and Netscape browsers
for browsers Opera and Chromium
